properties.descriptio: Royce's (1887) map shows a straight line between the point where the boundary line intersects a trail and the point where it meets the Broad River. If such a line was ever surveyed, no trace of it seems to remain.
According to Royce's (1887) map, the boundary line follows a watershed divide from the head of Shaw Creek to a point where a trail passes near the head of the North Fork of the Edisto River.
